      ggplot()

3. Aesthitic mappings

1) scatter plot

murders %>% 
  ggplot() + geom_point(aes(x = population / 10^6, y = total, color = region))

2) Layers

murders %>% 
  ggplot() + geom_point(aes(x = population / 10^6, y = total)) + 
  geom_text(aes(population/10^6, total, label = abb))

4. Arguments

1) nudge_x = , size =

murders %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = population / 10^6, y = total)) +
  geom_point(size = 3) + 
  geom_text(aes(label = abb), nudge_x = 1.5)

2) another geom_text()

global <- murders %>% ggplot(aes(x = population / 10^6, y = total, label = abb))
global + geom_point(size = 3) + geom_text(nudge_x = 1.5) + geom_text(aes(x = 10, y = 800, label = "Hello there~"))

3) scale_x_continous = , scale_y_continous =

Can change scale of aes and text

global <- murders %>% ggplot(aes(x = population / 10^6, y = total, label = abb))
global + 
  geom_point(size = 3) + 
  geom_text(nudge_x = 0.05) +
  scale_x_continuous(trans = "log10") +
  scale_y_continuous(trans = "log10")

4) another scaling and texting

# scale_x_continuous(trans = "log10") -> scale_x_log10() 
# scale_x_continuous(" ") -> labs(x = " " ) -> xlab(" ")
# scale_x_continuous(limits(c(n1, n2))) -> xlim(n1, n2)

5) coloring

global <- murders %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = population / 10^6, y = total, label = abb))
global + 
  geom_point(aes(color = region), size = 2) + 
  geom_text(nudge_x = 0.05) + 
  scale_x_continuous("population in log10", trans = "log10") + 
  scale_y_continuous("Total in log10", trans = "log10") + 
  ggtitle("US Gun Murders in 2010")

6) Annotation

r <- murders %>% 
  summarize(rate = sum(total)/ sum(population)*10^6) %>%
  pull(rate)

global <- murders %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = population / 10^6, y = total, label = abb))
global + 
  geom_point(aes(color = region), size = 3) + 
  geom_abline(intercept = log10(r)) + 
  geom_text(nudge_x = 0.05) +
  scale_x_continuous("Population in 100,000", trans = "log10") + 
  scale_y_continuous("Total numbre of murders", trans = "log10") + 
  ggtitle("US Gun Murders in 2010")

# scale_color_discrete(name = "Region") : Change legend name

7) Add-on packages

#ggthemes
library(ggthemes)
## Warning: package 'ggthemes' was built under R version 4.0.5
global <- murders %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = population / 10^6, y = total, label = abb))
global + 
  geom_point(aes(color = region), size = 3) + 
  geom_abline(intercept = log10(r), lty = 2, color = 'darkgrey') + 
  geom_text(nudge_x = 0.05) +
  scale_x_continuous("Population in 100,000", trans = "log10") + 
  scale_y_continuous("Total numbre of murders", trans = "log10") + 
  ggtitle("US Gun Murders in 2010") +
  theme_economist()
